main.binary_search(arr, x)[source]¶

In a nutshell, this search algorithm takes advantage of a collection of elements that is already sorted by ignoring half of the elements after just one comparison.

Parameters

  • arr – Integer Array

  • x – Integer number

Returns

If the number really exist in array the function will return index of the number in integer array. Else, the function will return -1.
